       title="Code blocks"
       id="Code_blocks">

    <p>Create multiline code blocks by placing triple backticks <code>```</code> before and after the code block.</p>
    <p>Optionally, specify the language name after the opening backticks to enable syntax highlighting.</p>
    <compare first-title="Markup" second-title="Result">
        <code-block lang="plain text">
            ```java
            class Main {

            public static void main(String[] args) {

            System.out.println("Enter two numbers");
            int first = 10;
            int second = 20;

            System.out.println(first + " " + second);

            // add two numbers
            int sum = first + second;
            System.out.println("The sum is: " + sum);
            }
            }
            ```
        </code-block>
        <code-block lang="java">
            class Main {

            public static void main(String[] args) {

            System.out.println("Enter two numbers");
