    <chapter title="Add prompt and highlight indentation" id="add-prompt-and-highlight-indentation">
        <p>To add a command line prompt at beginning of each line of code, add the <code>prompt</code> attribute.
            The code sample is copied without a prompt.</p>
        <p>It is useful for shell scripts and command examples.</p>
        <compare first-title="Markup" second-title="Result">
        <code-block lang="plain text">
                        ```shell
                        sudo tar -xzf the-package-*.tar.gz -C /opt
                        ```
                        {prompt="$"}
                    </code-block>

                        <code-block lang="Shell" prompt="$" >
                            sudo tar -xzf the-package-*.tar.gz -C /opt
                        </code-block>
        </compare>
        <p>To highlight the indentation in the code fragment, use the <code>show-white-spaces</code> attribute.
            This is handy if the code block has a complex indentation or formatting and you need to highlight this.</p>
        <compare first-title="Markup" second-title="Result">
        <code-block lang="C">
                        ```c
                        public string Name
                        {
                            get
                            set
                        }

                        public int Age
                        {
                            get
                            set
                        }
                        ```
                        {show-white-spaces="true"}
                    </code-block>
                    <code-block lang="C" show-white-spaces="true">
                        public string Name
                        {
                            get;
                            set;
                        }

                        public int Age
                        {
                            get;
                            set;
                        }
                    </code-block>
        </compare>
